    <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
      <body>
        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="Aink426-kilavi">vēntaṟkut tāṉait talaivaṉāy oḻukum talaimakaṉ pirintu viṉaimuṭittu vantu talaiviyōṭu uṟaikiṉṟuḻi iṉṉum piriyum kol eṉṟu karutiya talaimakaṭkuk kavaṟci tīrac colliyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">The hero, whose conduct was such that he was the head of the king's army, having separated, completed his task, returned and now staying with the heroine, to the heroine was thinking 'will he separate?', in order to end [her] concern, spoke [this].</p> 
            </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
          <lg xml:id="Aink426">        
            <l>veṉvēl vēnta ṉaruntoḻi ṟuṟantiṉi</l>
            <l>naṉṉutal yāṉē celavoḻin taṉeṉē</l>
            <l>muracupā ṭatira vēvi</l>
            <l>yaracupaṭak kaṭakku maruñcamat tāṉē.</l>          
                       </lg>   
                       <lg xml:lang="en">
                        <l>The king with the victious spear,</l> 
                         <l>who urges on [the army] so the drums shook</l>
                          <l>and overcome [enemy] kings so [they] fall in difficult battle</l> 
                          <l>-- now he has abondoned the difficult task,</l>
                          <l>O one with the good forehead,</l>    
                        <l>I have stopped [my] journey.</l>
                                               </lg>
        </div>
      </body>
